posts.com: This is the best tag match I've seen in TJPW. This was a fitting end to the 3rd Max Heart tournament as that's what was on display from both teams in this match. Shoko and Misao came in as the more cerebral team, using spray to gain an advantage that they would maintain for a lot of the match. They targeted Maki's left arm early, but they really went to work taking apart Miyu's right leg after Misao threw it into the corner post. This could've been even better if the limb work had more effect later in the match, like Maki or Miyu being unable to hit one of their big moves effectively. Even still, the damage done early made Maki and Miyu sympathetic figures in the match and helped to isolate Maki for a lot of the match. There was an incredible moment where Miyu caught Shoko with a kick to the head on a dive that helped turn the tide of the match. Maki and Shoko were the two legal wrestlers for pretty much the last half of the match, and their fight was intense and emotional. Maki and Miyu were able to fire each other up and hit a cool diving DDT/German suplex combo to set up the win. This is the new high watermark for tag wrestling in TJPW.
